description:
Tamoor Hussain and Lucy James chat about the hour they got to see of Dragon Age: The Veilguard at Summer Game Fest.

Dragon Age: The Veilguard, formerly known as Dreadwolf, was announced way back in 2018, but it didn't get more than a brief teaser over the next five-plus years. The game was fully unveiled during the Xbox Games Showcase on June 9 and will launch in Fall 2024 for Xbox Series X|S, PS5 and PC.
title: Dragon Age: The Veilguard Is a Great Start For Newcomers | Summer Game Fest 2024

description: It's a triple feature! First up is Black Voice in Gaming, a show that celebrates and highlights Black developers and their games. Second is Dames 4 Games, a showcase of games by women, for women. The last is Stream for a Cause, which empowers streamers to fundraise for their communities.
title: Black Voices in Gaming, Dames 4 Games, Stream for a Cause

description:
Rally the Veilguard and defy the gods in Dragon Age: The Veilguard, coming fall 2024

This bold, heroic adventure is built to deliver on what Dragon Age is best known for: rich storytelling, fantasy worldbuilding, companions and fellowship, and a world where you matter.
 
It's time to become the leader others believe in. Select from different races and combat classes, customize your appearance, choose your character’s backstory and begin your journey as Rook, Dragon Age’s newest hero. Be who you want to be and play how you want to play as you fight back and lead your team of seven companions, each with their own rich stories.
title: Dragon Age: The Veilguard | Official Gameplay Reveal Trailer

description:
